    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed per MRL 2 requirements. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD model reliably predicts relative hemolysis index within acceptance bounds across the CPB operating envelope. The hemolysis damage accumulation methodology, informed by the power-law scalar transport refinements described in the peer-reviewed literature (see referencesIdentifier), provides adequate predictive fidelity for the intended regulatory decision. Model accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
